ce:section.ce:para:
The fluorescence measurements can be performed using any fluorescence spectrophotometer able to acquire fluorescence/emission maps (i.e. acquiring different emission spectra as the excitation wavelength is changed). The optimal choice in terms of resolution and time of acquisition is instrument dependent, typical instrumental settings are the following:

                           -

Excitation range: 270–475 nm;


                           -

Emission range: 350–700 nm;


                           -

Excitation increment: 5 nm;


                           -

Excitation/emission slit width: 3 nm/3 nm;


                           -

Sampling interval: 2 nm.
